{
  "texts": [
    "Although patient EMRs are kept in a digital environment, this environment is generally local.",
    "Additionally, the authority over EMRs usually belongs to the hospitals.",
    "Although patients have the right to access their own EMRs, the authority to share their data is unclear.Hospital EMRs consist of large volumes that need to be stored securely, processed effectively, and shared without delay.",
    "Keeping EMRs in a public database to create big data ensures comprehensive access to patient data [1].",
    "In this way, a patient's medical records can be evaluated by different entities."
  ]
}